			<br style="display:none;"/>

			<div class="comment_text">
			<p>I&#8217;ve been searching now and again for information about the ifferent DVCS, and some time ago I found a nice side-by-side comparision of Mercurial and Bazaar: </p>
<p><a href="http://sayspy.blogspot.com/2006/11/bazaar-vs-mercurial-unscientific.html" rel="nofollow">http://sayspy.blogspot.com/2006/11/bazaar-vs-mercurial-unscientific.html</a></p>
<p>It confirmed my gut feeling to choose Mercurial (almost a year ago, now). </p>
<p>And Mercurial also has a Windows installer:<br />
<a href="http://www.selenic.com/mercurial/wiki/index.cgi/BinaryPackages" rel="nofollow">http://www.selenic.com/mercurial/wiki/index.cgi/BinaryPackages</a><br />
-&gt; <a href="http://mercurial.berkwood.com/" rel="nofollow">http://mercurial.berkwood.com/</a></p>
<p>Best wishes, and thanks for the nice article!</p>
