	<dd class="comment even thread-even depth-1 commentlist_item highlander-comment" id="comment-4504">

		<div class="comment" id="div-comment-4504">
			<strong class="comment-author vcard author" style="height:32px;line-height:32px;">
			
			<span class="fn">Pocho</span></strong> <span class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><small>(04:39:39)</small> : </span>
			
			<br style="display:none;"/>

			<div class="comment_text">
			<p>If you want to automatically create keep files for empty directories, here is a Python script that&#8217;ll do just that.</p>
<p><code><br />
import os<br />
from os.path import join, getsize<br />
for root, dirs, files in os.walk('C:/proyects/myproject'):<br />
    print root, "... ",<br />
    if len(dirs) == 0 and len(files) == 0:<br />
        open(root + "/keep", 'w')<br />
        print "creating keep"<br />
    else:<br />
        print ''</p>
<p>os.system('pause')<br />
</code></p>
			</div>
